i## Project lueur	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThis project is called lueur, pronounced \lɥœʁ\, which is a	/	tilde.team	70
iFrench word for vivid, momentary expression.	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
i### How it works	/	tilde.team	70
i	/	tilde.team	70
iThe way the project works is deliberately very simple: I	/	tilde.team	70
iretrieve the text in Markdown format, which can contain	/	tilde.team	70
iHTML. The text is then passed to the Markdown parser, which	/	tilde.team	70
ireturns an AST that is traversed to produce the final	/	tilde.team	70
ioutput. The goldmark project was used to parse the Markdown	/	tilde.team	70
iand the Go Networking project for the HTML.	/	tilde.team	70
hgoldmark	URL:https://github.com/yuin/goldmark	github.com	443
hGo Networking	URL:https://cs.opensource.google/go/x/net/+/master:html/	cs.opensource.google	443
